preCrisis_log_branwen_seal_17b.body:
// MAINTENANCE LOG — BRANWEN YARDS
// SECTION 17-B / DECK NINETEEN
// Logged by: Foreman Cael Branwen, Day 84 of the year of the second pass

Second shift report. The corridor's atmospheric flow keeps reading wrong on the Halen-Coil sensors but the actual readings on the calibration kit say clean. I've sent it back twice. The ship doesn't want me here.

Lost Eddins yesterday. He went to check the filtration on the third compartment in and didn't come back for three hours. When he did he was quiet for the rest of the shift. He didn't lose anything, didn't see anything. He just stopped wanting to talk. He filed his next-shift slip and didn't show up.

I'm sealing 17-B. The compartment is doing something to people. The ship is doing something to people. I don't know which.

— Cael Branwen, sealing this section by my own hand.

voss_daughter_card.body:
// HANDLE-ACCESS CARD — laminated, edges softened by years of handling

Handle: TARA-V
Issue: Bureau familial dependent, dependent class A
Clearance: maintenance levels only

// On the back, in small handwriting that doesn't look like Bureau script:
//
// 'I told her not to take the relay shift alone.
//  I told her four times.
//  She said the work paid double.
//  I said the Bureau pays double when the risk is real.
//
//  This card is all that came back.'
//
// — V.

